eus/en-US/docs/next/stores\">Stores</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/exporting\">Static Exporting</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/intro\">Plugins</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/functional\">Functional Actions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/control\">Control Actions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/using\">Using Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/tinker\">The <code>tinker</code> Action</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/writing\">Writing Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/security\">Security Considerations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/plugins/publishing\">Publishing Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/deploying/intro\">Deploying</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/deploying/serverful\">Server Deployment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/deploying/serverless\">Serverless Deployment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/deploying/size\">Optimizing Code Size</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/deploying/relative-paths\">Relative Paths</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/deploying/docker\">Docker Deployment</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/updating\">Migrating from v0.2.x</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/pitfalls-and-bugs\">Common Pitfalls and Known Bugs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h1>Advanced</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/advanced/intro\">Under the Hood</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/advanced/arch\">Architecture</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/advanced/initial-loads\">Initial Loads</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/advanced/subsequent-loads\">Subsequent Loads</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/advanced/routing\">Routing</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/advanced/define_app\"><code>define_app</code> in Detail</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></aside></div></div></div><div class=\"h-full flex w-full\" data-hk=\"3.21\"><div data-hk=\"3.22\" class=\"px-3 w-full sm:mr-auto sm:ml-auto sm:max-w-prose lg:max-w-3xl xl:max-w-4xl 2xl:max-w-5xl\"><!--#--><div class=\"ring-4 ring-orange-400 p-4 rounded-lg mt-1\" data-hk=\"3.23\"><div class=\"flex flex-col 2xs:flex-row dark:text-white\" data-hk=\"3.24\"><span data-hk=\"3.25\" style=\"fill: #fb923c;\" class=\"self-center mr-2\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"auto\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"2.25rem\" fill=\"\\#000000\"><path d=\"M12 7c.55 0 1 .45 1 1v4c0 .55-.45 1-1 1s-1-.45-1-1V8c0-.55.45-1 1-1zm-.01-5C6.47 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.47 10 9.99 10C17.52 22 22 17.52 22 12S17.52 2 11.99 2zM12 20c-4.42 0-8-3.58-8-8s3.58-8 8-8 8 3.58 8 8-3.58 8-8 8zm1-3h-2v-2h2v2z\"/></svg></span><p data-hk=\"3.26\">This version of the documentation is for a version that has not yet been released, and features documented here may not be present in the latest release. You can see the latest stable version of the docs <a href=\"en-US/docs/0.3.x/intro\" class=\"underline\">here</a>.</p></div></div><!--/--><main data-hk=\"3.27\" class=\"text-black dark:text-white\"><div class=\"markdown\" data-hk=\"2.0\"><h1>Migrating from v0.2.x</h1>\n<p>Perseus v0.3.0 added significant architectural changes to Perseus under the hood, and also made it easier to use for you! Additionally, this update provides inbuilt deployment functionality for moving Perseus to production (though that's not recommended yet)! If you're currently running v0.2.x, here's how to upgrade!</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Update your <code>Cargo.toml</code> dependencies for <code>perseus</code> to <code>0.3</code>.</li>\n<li>Upgrade the Perseus CLI with <code>cargo install perseus-cli</code>.</li>\n<li>Run <code>perseus clean</code> to remove the old <code>.perseus/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Remove any custom config managers you may have, they've been replaced by <a href=\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/stores\">mutable and immutable stores</a>.</li>\n<li>Take anything Perseus-related wrapped in <code>Rc::new</code> (these will be all through your template definitions and error pages) and remove the <code>Rc::new</code>, Perseus now handles that internally, with no performance cost!</li>\n<li>If you're using i18n, add the <code>translator-fluent</code> flag to <code>perseus</code> in your <code>Cargo.toml</code>. If you're not, your Wasm bundle size has been reduced!</li>\n<li>Change any uses of the <code>HOST</code> and <code>PORT</code> environment variables to the <code>--host</code> and <code>--port</code> flags on <code>perseus serve</code> in development, and use <code>PERSEUS_HOST</code> and <code>PERSEUS_PORT</code> in production. The original environment variable names will still work in deployments, but they'll be deprecated in v0.4.0. </li>\n<li>Update your code for the remaining breaking changes listed in <a href=\"https://github.com/arctic-hen7/perseus/blob/main/CHANGELOG\">the CHANGELOG</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Perseus v0.3.0 also changed a few common idioms, like breaking out the <code>.template()</code> call into a separate function <code>template_fn()</code>. This is no longer recommended, though it will still work fine. You can check out the <a href=\"https://github.com/arctic-hen7/perseus/tree/main/examples\">examples directory</a> to see how things are a bit nicer now in terms of formatting.</p>\n<h2>If You've Ejected</h2>\n<p>If you were running Perseus v0.2.x and had ejected, here are the steps you should take in addition to the above.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Rename <code>.perseus/</code> to <code>.perseus.old/</code>.</li>\n<li>Run <code>perseus build</code> to create a new <code>.perseus/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Apply your changes to the new directory.</li>\n<li>Delete <code>.perseus.old/</code> when you're done.</li>\n<li>Confirm everything works with <code>perseus serve</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This may seem arduous, but v0.3.0 includes notable updates to the innards in <code>.perseus/</code>, and it's typically simpler to re-apply your own changes to the new system than it is to apply Perseus' updates to your existing directory (though you could do this if you really wanted).</p>\n</div></main></div></div></div></div><footer class=\"w-full flex justify-center py-5 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-navy-deep\" data-hk=\"3.28\"><p data-hk=\"3.29\" class=\"dark:text-white mx-5 text-center\"><span data-hk=\"3.30\">© <a href=\"https://github.com/arctic-hen7\" class=\"underline\">arctic-hen7</a> ⁨2021⁩, see license <a href=\"https://github.com/arctic-hen7/perseus/blob/main/LICENSE\" class=\"underline\">here</a>.</span></p></footer><script defer=\"\" data-hk=\"2.1\" src=\".perseus/static/prism.js\"></script><script data-hk=\"2.2\">window.Prism.highlightAll();</script>","state":"{\"title\":\"Migrating from v0.2.x\",\"content\":\"<h1>Migrating from v0.2.x</h1>\\n<p>Perseus v0.3.0 added significant architectural changes to Perseus under the hood, and also made it easier to use for you! Additionally, this update provides inbuilt deployment functionality for moving Perseus to production (though that's not recommended yet)! If you're currently running v0.2.x, here's how to upgrade!</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Update your <code>Cargo.toml</code> dependencies for <code>perseus</code> to <code>0.3</code>.</li>\\n<li>Upgrade the Perseus CLI with <code>cargo install perseus-cli</code>.</li>\\n<li>Run <code>perseus clean</code> to remove the old <code>.perseus/</code> directory.</li>\\n<li>Remove any custom config managers you may have, they've been replaced by <a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/stores\\\">mutable and immutable stores</a>.</li>\\n<li>Take anything Perseus-related wrapped in <code>Rc::new</code> (these will be all through your template definitions and error pages) and remove the <code>Rc::new</code>, Perseus now handles that internally, with no performance cost!</li>\\n<li>If you're using i18n, add the <code>translator-fluent</code> flag to <code>perseus</code> in your <code>Cargo.toml</code>. If you're not, your Wasm bundle size has been reduced!</li>\\n<li>Change any uses of the <code>HOST</code> and <code>PORT</code> environment variables to the <code>--host</code> and <code>--port</code> flags on <code>perseus serve</code> in development, and use <code>PERSEUS_HOST</code> and <code>PERSEUS_PORT</code> in production. The original environment variable names will still work in deployments, but they'll be deprecated in v0.4.0. </li>\\n<li>Update your code for the remaining breaking changes listed in <a href=\\\"https://github.com/arctic-hen7/perseus/blob/main/CHANGELOG\\\">the CHANGELOG</a>.</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>Perseus v0.3.0 also changed a few common idioms, like breaking out the <code>.template()</code> call into a separate function <code>template_fn()</code>. This is no longer recommended, though it will still work fine. You can check out the <a href=\\\"https://github.com/arctic-hen7/perseus/tree/main/examples\\\">examples directory</a> to see how things are a bit nicer now in terms of formatting.</p>\\n<h2>If You've Ejected</h2>\\n<p>If you were running Perseus v0.2.x and had ejected, here are the steps you should take in addition to the above.</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Rename <code>.perseus/</code> to <code>.perseus.old/</code>.</li>\\n<li>Run <code>perseus build</code> to create a new <code>.perseus/</code> directory.</li>\\n<li>Apply your changes to the new directory.</li>\\n<li>Delete <code>.perseus.old/</code> when you're done.</li>\\n<li>Confirm everything works with <code>perseus serve</code>.</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>This may seem arduous, but v0.3.0 includes notable updates to the innards in <code>.perseus/</code>, and it's typically simpler to re-apply your own changes to the new system than it is to apply Perseus' updates to your existing directory (though you could do this if you really wanted).</p>\\n\",\"sidebar_content\":\"<h1>Introduction</h1>\\n<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/intro\\\">Introduction</a>\\n<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/what-is-perseus\\\">What is Perseus?</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/hello-world\\\">Hello World!</a></li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/second-app\\\">Your Second App</a></li>\\n</ul>\\n<hr />\\n<h1>Reference</h1>\\n<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/define-app\\\"><code>define_app!</code></a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/views\\\">Writing Views</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/debugging\\\">Debugging</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/templates/intro\\\">Templates and Routing</a>\\n<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/templates/metadata-modification\\\">Modifying the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code></a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://arctic-hen7.github.io/perseus/en-US/docs/next/templates/setting-header